children.text: HTML

HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup Language. This language describes the structure of web pages that the user sees and interacts with such as buttons, text, and the other parts of the web page. It is a text-based code that we write so that web browsers like safari, google chrome can understand and display it to the user. They are basically saved with a  .html extension.

The webpage for the HTML code looks something like this:
Before understanding the above example let us discuss what HTML tags and elements are:
HTML tags:
These are the keywords that are used to create webpages and are enclosed within  < > these(angular) brackets. The closing tags contain a forward slash(/). Certain tags do need a closing tag.
HTML elements:

These elements are responsible for creating web pages and defining content on that webpage. An element in HTML usually consists of a start tag <tag name>, a close tag </tag name>, and content inserted between them. Technically, an element is a collection of start tags, attributes, end tags, and content between them.
Note:
In HTML the indentation in code is for readability only, whereas in python without indentation you will be getting an indentation error.
Now let us go through every line of the above example in detail and see how this program works:
The first line
<!DOCTYPE html>
is a DOCTYPE declaration. It tells the web browser what version of the HTML we are using on this particular web page.
HTML5 is the latest version of HTML. So, it tells the browser that we are using the HTML5 version.
The next line <html> indicates the beginning of the HTML content of our web page and </html> indicates the end of the HTML  content of the page.

In this HTML tag  “<html lang = “en” >” we notice a word lang i.e language which is called an HTML attribute. It provides additional information about the Html tag. Here, the lang attribute tells the web browser or anyone looking at the HTML of the page that this page is written in a language, and the language which is written here is English.

The <head> tag in HTML is used to define the head portion of the document which contains information related to the document. And inside the head tag, we see the <title> tag followed by the closing </title> tag. In between these tags, there is “Hello!” which means the title of this page should be the word “Hello!”.Then the head tag is closed.

The next line <body> is the visible part of the webpage that the user can see.  The main content goes in the <body> tag. Multiple tags can be used to create different content on the webpage. When someone visits this webpage, the text “Hello, world!” will be displayed on the page. Then the body is closed.
DOM
DOM stands for Document Object Model which is a tree-like structure that describes how all these elements relate to each other.

The above picture shows the tree shape diagram for the code we wrote earlier. Here, the HTML element is the parent node and has two child elements inside it. A head element and a body element. Inside the head element, we have the title element and inside the title element we have the text “Hello!”. In the same way, inside the body element, we have the text “Hello, world!”.
